<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbf2f44da-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s10803"><num value="10803">§ 10803.</num><heading> Allotments</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall make allotments under this subchapter to eligible systems to establish and administer systems—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbf2f44db-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s10803/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> which meet the requirements of <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s10805">section 10805 of this title</ref>; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbf2f44dc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s10803/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><chapeau> which are designed to—</chapeau><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idbf2f44dd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s10803/2/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> protect and advocate the rights of individuals with mental illness; and</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idbf2f44de-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s10803/2/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> investigate incidents of abuse and neglect of individuals with mental illness if the incidents are reported to the system or if there is probable cause to believe that the incidents occurred.</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idbf2f44df-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/319/tI/s103">Pub. L. 99–319, title I, § 103</ref>, <date date="1986-05-23">May 23, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/479">100 Stat. 479</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/102/173/s10/2">Pub. L. 102–173, § 10(2)</ref>, <date date="1991-11-27">Nov. 27, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/1219">105 Stat. 1219</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbf2f44e0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idbf2f44e1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idbf2f44e2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1991—Par. (2). <ref href="/us/pl/102/173">Pub. L. 102–173</ref> substituted “individuals with mental illness” for “mentally ill individuals” in two places.</p>
</note>
</notes>
